sentences: Since 1949, he was a regular member of the Slovenian Academy of Sciences and Arts (SAZU).
He became a regular member of SAZU on December 6, 1949.
He not only composed for the piano but also the violin, the clarinet and the bassoon in 1952.
Škerjanc received the Prešeren Award four times, in 1947 for his Concert for Violin and Orchestra (Slovene: Koncert za violino in orkester), and then again in 1948, 1950 and 1971.
In 2001, he was commemorated by appearing on a postage stamp of Slovenia which featured at portrait of him by Božidar Jakac positioned on the manuscript of his symphonic poem Marenka.

sentences: Lucijan Marija Škerjanc (December 17, 1900 – February 27, 1973) was a Slovene composer, music pedagogue, conductor, musician, and writer who was accomplished on and wrote for a number of musical instruments such as the piano, violin and clarinet.
Škerjanc belongs among the most important older composers of modern Slovene music and is a key Slovenian music personality of the 20th century.

He spent many years teaching composition at the Ljubljana Academy of Music, teaching composers such as Nada Ludvig-Pečar whilst serving as a chancellor for a period and was a pianist, conductor, music writer, and director of the Slovenian Philharmonic Orchestra based in the country's capital.
